text.section:
The authority granted under the provisions of this section may not be exercised unless and until the Secretary determines in writing that its exercise:
Is required to provide access to or egress from the Port of Baltimore for international freight;
Will not cause extraordinary damage to roads and bridges in the State or require extraordinary expense for the maintenance of those roads and bridges;
Will not cause undue adverse environmental impact upon or unduly disrupt residential neighborhoods; and
Will not impair highway safety.
